The paper focuses on the analysis of purchased Twitter followers and their behavior, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to predict suspicious follower behavior, which falls under the category of cybersecurity and privacy. Therefore, cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of content sharing and behavioral patterns, which falls under the category of data mining and analysis. Therefore, cs.SD (Software Development) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image analysis to identify fraudulent accounts, which falls under the category of multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely sub-category.
